Both *nbnte‘us and nr'mtius are contracted from *noventius (·new-comer').— recuperatorem: recuperatores were a special kind of judges or jurymen, who were appointed, instead of ordinary iudices, to decide certain classes of suits, primarily those in which international relations were involved, as claims sor money between Romans and peregrini: the matter is, however, not fully understood. A iudex may be public (belonging to one of the regularly constituted boards) or private (appointed by the magistrate for a particular private suit).
